27 SECTION 2. IC 9-18.5-37 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
28 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
29 JULY 1, 2026]:
30 Chapter 37. Epilepsy Foundation Trust License Plates
31 Sec. 1. The bureau shall design and issue an epilepsy foundation
32 trust license plate. The epilepsy foundation trust license plate shall
33 be designed and issued as a special group recognition license plate
34 under IC 9-18.5-12 and must include the following:
35 (1) A basic design for the plate, with consecutive numbers or
36 letters, or both, to properly identify the vehicle.
37 (2) A background design, an emblem, or colors that designate
38 the license plate as an epilepsy foundation trust license plate.
39 (3) Any other information the bureau considers necessary.
40 Sec. 2. A person that is eligible to register a vehicle under this
41 title is eligible to receive an epilepsy foundation trust license plate
42 under this chapter upon doing the following:
2026 IN 1171—LS 6233/DI 137

3
1 (1) Completing an application for an epilepsy foundation trust
2 license plate.
3 (2) Paying the fees under section 3 of this chapter.
4 Sec. 3. (a) The bureau shall collect the following fees for an
5 epilepsy foundation trust license plate:
6 (1) An annual supplemental fee of fifteen dollars ($15) under
7 IC 9-18.5-12-16.
8 (2) An annual fee of not more than twenty-five dollars ($25)
9 under IC 9-18.5-12-14(d)(2) or IC 9-18.5-12-15(b).
10 (b) The bureau shall collect the annual fee described in
11 subsection (a)(2) and deposit the annual fee in the epilepsy
12 foundation trust fund established by section 4 of this chapter.
13 Sec. 4. (a) The epilepsy foundation trust fund is established.
14 (b) The treasurer of state shall invest the money in the epilepsy
15 foundation trust fund not currently needed to meet the obligations
16 of the epilepsy foundation trust fund in the same manner as other
17 public trust funds are invested. Interest that accrues from these
18 investments shall be deposited in the epilepsy foundation trust
19 fund.
20 (c) The bureau shall administer the epilepsy foundation trust
21 fund. Expenses of administering the epilepsy foundation trust fund
22 shall be paid from money in the epilepsy foundation trust fund.
23 (d) The bureau shall distribute at least one (1) time each month
24 the money from the epilepsy foundation trust fund to the Epilepsy
25 Foundation Indiana.
26 (e) Money in the epilepsy foundation trust fund at the end of the
27 state fiscal year does not revert to the state general fund.
